3️⃣ Query Azure Resource Graph (Inventario Premium)

Kql

Resources
| where type == "microsoft.web/sites"
| where kind contains "functionapp"
| extend serverFarmId = tostring(properties.serverFarmId)
| join kind=leftouter (
    Resources
    | where type == "microsoft.web/serverfarms"
    | project serverFarmId = id,
              sku = tostring(sku.name),
              tier = tostring(sku.tier),
              capacity = tostring(sku.capacity)
) on serverFarmId
| where tier contains "Premium"
| project
    subscriptionId,
    resourceGroup,
    functionName = name,
    location,
    sku,
    capacity,
    serverFarmId
| order by subscriptionId asc

4️⃣ Métricas Técnicas – Queries KQL
✅ 4.1 Execution Count por día (30 / 90 días)

Kql

requests
| where timestamp > ago(30d)
| summarize ExecutionCount = count() by bin(timestamp, 1d), cloud_RoleName
| summarize
    AvgPerDay = avg(ExecutionCount),
    MaxPerDay = max(ExecutionCount),
    ActiveDays = dcount(timestamp)
by cloud_RoleName
| extend SporadicUsage = iff(ActiveDays < 10, "Yes", "No")
| order by AvgPerDay asc

✅ 4.2 CPU Promedio y Máximo

Kql

AzureMetrics
| where TimeGenerated > ago(30d)
| where MetricName == "CpuPercentage"
| summarize
    AvgCPU = avg(Average),
    MaxCPU = max(Maximum)
by Resource
| order by AvgCPU asc

✅ 4.3 Memory Working Set

Kql

performanceCounters
| where timestamp > ago(30d)
| where counterName == "Working Set"
| summarize
    AvgMemoryMB = avg(counterValue) / 1024 / 1024,
    MaxMemoryMB = max(counterValue) / 1024 / 1024
by cloud_RoleName

✅ 4.4 Instancias Activas

Kql

AzureMetrics
| where MetricName == "InstanceCount"
| summarize
    AvgInstances = avg(Average),
    MaxInstances = max(Maximum)
by Resource

✅ 4.5 Heatmap Horario

Kql

requests
| where timestamp > ago(30d)
| summarize Executions=count() by cloud_RoleName, hourofday(timestamp)
| render heatmap

✅ 4.6 Functions activas sin tráfico externo

Kql

requests
| where timestamp > ago(30d)
| summarize TotalRequests=count() by cloud_RoleName
| where TotalRequests == 0


Cruzar con métricas de CPU > 0 para detectar procesos internos.

5️⃣ Modelo de Scoring (FinOps)
🎯 Variables
Métrica	Peso
Avg ejecuciones/día	30%
Avg CPU %	25%
Memoria promedio	15%
Uso de instancias	20%
Patrón esporádico	10%
🧮 Score ejemplo

Text

Score = 
(ExecutionScore * 0.3) +
(CPUScore * 0.25) +
(MemoryScore * 0.15) +
(InstanceScore * 0.2) +
(SporadicScore * 0.1)

🏷 Clasificación
Score	Clasificación
> 70	Óptima
40 – 70	Potencial optimización
< 40	Subutilizada crítica
6️⃣ Estimación FinOps – Ahorro Potencial
Premium EP1 ejemplo:

~€150–200 / instancia / mes

Si:

Avg CPU < 5%
Avg ejecuciones < 100/día
Always Ready > 1

➡ Posible cambio a Consumption o reducción de instancias.

Fórmula simple:

Text

Ahorro estimado = 
(Capacidad actual – Capacidad recomendada) × Precio mensual SKU

7️⃣ Recomendaciones Técnicas
✅ Rightsizing

Reducir EP3 → EP1

✅ Reducción pre-warmed instances

Configurar:

Bash

az functionapp plan update \
  --number-of-workers 1

✅ Migración a Consumption

Si:

Baja latencia no es crítica
Sin VNET dedicada
Sin requisitos Always Ready
✅ Consolidación

Unificar múltiples Functions en un mismo plan Premium.

